gus, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Angus, Scotland":"Forfar, Forfarshire, Schotland","Scotland":"Schotland","Mearns, Kincardineshire, Scotland":"Kincardineshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Forfarshire, Scotland":"Forfarshire, Schotland","Forfar, Angusshire, Scotland":"Forfar, Angus, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1100–1201":"1100–1201","1090–1118":"1090–1118","1125–1171":"1125–1171","1118–1187":"1118–1187","1080–Male":"1080–Deceased","1080–Female":"1080–Deceased","1118":"1118","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","1125":"1125","1201":"1201","1100":"1100","Abt 1117":"about 1117","1187":"1187","1171":"1171","Forfarshire, Angushire, Scotland":"Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom","Angus, Scotland":"Forfar, Forfarshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Mearns, Kincardineshire, Scotland":"Kincardineshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Forfarshire, Scotland":"Forfarshire, Scotland","Forfar, Angusshire, Scotland":"Forfar, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Mearns","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from the district of The Mearns, an alternative name for Kincardineshire, or from Mearns in Renfrewshire. The placenames derive from Gaelic <i>An Mhaoirne</i> ‘the Stewartry, area under the jurisdiction of a steward’, and is also known to have been adopted in Ireland for <b>Ó Mearáin</b>, see   Marron  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Marron","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Jesus, Armando, Juan, Mario, Carlos, Enrique, Joaquin, Rafael, Alfonso, Alfredo, Alvaro.  Irish Ciaran, Parnell.","Irish (Monaghan): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Mearáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Mearán</i>’, a personal name from a diminutive of <i>mear</i> ‘lively’. Compare   Merry  . There may have been some confusion with   Marrin  .","Spanish (<b>Marrón</b>): nickname from <i>marrón</i> ‘brown’, a word of French origin."]},{"name":"Marn","meanings":["Scottish and English: variant of <b>Marne</b>, which is perhaps a variant of   Mearns   with loss of final <i>-s</i> or else possibly a variant of   Morrin   1.","Slovenian: nickname from an old spelling of the archaic adjective <i>maren</i> meaning ‘diligent’, but also ‘worthless’. Compare   Maren  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Fynuella Mearns was born in 1100, in Kincardineshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, her father, Mearns, was 21 and her mother, Maria Mearns, was 21. She married Dufagan Mac Indreachtaich 1st about 1117, in Forfar, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1201, in Forfar, Forfarshire, Scotland, at the age of 101, and was buried in Scotland."},"et":{"1100–1201":"1100–1201","1090–1118":"1090–1118","1125–1171":"1125–1171","1118–1187":"1118–1187","1080–Male":"1080–Surnud","1080–Female":"1080–Surnud","1118":"1118","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","1125":"1125","1201":"1201","1100":"1100","Abt 1117":"umbes 1117","1187":"1187","1171":"1171","Forfarshire, Angushire, Scotland":"Angus, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Angus, Scotland":"Forfar, Forfarshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Mearns, Kincardineshire, Scotland":"Kincardineshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Forfarshire, Scotland":"Forfarshire, Scotland","Forfar, Angusshire, Scotland":"Forfar, Angus, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1100–1201":"1100–1201","1090–1118":"1090–1118","1125–1171":"1125–1171","1118–1187":"1118–1187","1080–Male":"1080–Kuollut","1080–Female":"1080–Kuollut","1118":"1118","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","1125":"1125","1201":"1201","1100":"1100","Abt 1117":"noin 1117","1187":"1187","1171":"1171","Forfarshire, Angushire, Scotland":"Angus, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Angus, Scotland":"Forfar, Forfarshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Mearns, Kincardineshire, Scotland":"Kincardineshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Forfarshire, Scotland":"Forfarshire, Scotland","Forfar, Angusshire, Scotland":"Forfar, Angus, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},